    <briefdescription>
<para>Lightweight trace buffer — timestamped event recorder. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Records events (id + optional 16-bit value) into a fixed-size circular buffer for post-mortem debugging. No UART, no printf — just stamp and store. Read it out with a debugger or dump over CLI.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="structSYN__TraceEntry" kindref="compound">SYN_TraceEntry</ref><sp/>entries[64];</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="structSYN__Trace" kindref="compound">SYN_Trace</ref><sp/>trace;</highlight></codeline>
